{
  "type": "spell",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"ddb\">\n<p>Until the spell ends, ice rimes your body, and you gain the following benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>You are immune to &amp;Reference[cold]{cold} damage and have resistance to &amp;Reference[fire]{fire} damage.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>You can move across difficult terrain created by ice or snow without spending extra movement.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>The ground in a 10-foot radius around you is icy and is difficult terrain for creatures other than you. The radius moves with you.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>You can use your action to create a 15-foot &amp;Reference[cone]{cone} of freezing wind extending from your outstretched hand in a direction you choose. Each creature in the &amp;Reference[cone]{cone} must make a &amp;Reference[con]{Constitution} saving throw. A creature takes 4d6 &amp;Reference[cold]{cold} damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. A creature that fails its save against this effect has its speed halved until the start of your next turn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>",
